---
SH caveats
---
compatibility
-- zsh
---- tested; NOT WORKING
  >> IFS splitting in zsh is NOT posix compliant
-- dash
---- tested; working
-- bash
---- tested; working
-- ash
---- untested; likely to work
-- yash
---- untested; likely to work
---
mkdir
-- mkdir is only needed during push(),pull() and grab() to create folders
-- however if they already exist mkdir is never needed
---
curl
-- curl is only used in grab() if cloning outside of $push_path
-- otherwise data will be cloned from $push_path
---
